# IMPORTANT — why the live site can stay blank even after Lovable Cloud → Secrets:
# Cloud Secrets are often injected for Supabase Edge Functions only, NOT for `vite build`.
# If brivano.io (or GitHub → Vercel/Netlify/Cloudflare) builds without env, the JS bundle has no Supabase URL/key.
# Fix: add these as build-time env on the system that runs `npm run build`:
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#   VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY   (same value as Supabase "anon public" key)
# GitHub: repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → add the two names above.
# Docs: https://docs.lovable.dev/tips-tricks/external-deployment-hosting
#
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` (never commit `.env`). Lovable editor `.env.example` alone does nothing.
# Optional aliases vite.config also reads: sb_url + sb_anon, SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, VITE_SB_URL + VITE_SB_ANON.
# No quotes. Remove VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID everywhere — unused. Never put SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY in the frontend.

# Scraper backend (Trulia/Hotpads, Skip Trace).
# Local:   http://localhost:8080
# Deployed: set your Railway URL
# VITE_SCRAPER_BACKEND_URL=https://your-app.up.railway.app

# Optional tables (if your Supabase schema omits some scraper tables)
# VITE_SKIP_OPTIONAL_TABLES=true

# Optional: show Admin on production for these emails (comma-separated).
# VITE_ADMIN_EMAILS=info@brivano.io,admin@brivano.io

# Supabase — required at BUILD time. URL + anon key must be from the same project (Settings → API).
# Either use VITE_* (preferred) OR plain names below — vite.config maps SUPABASE_* → client (service role is never bundled).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_anon_public_key
# Same values, Lovable-style names (also work):
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_public_key
# Never put SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY in the frontend repo or Lovable "public" env — server only. Never commit real keys.
